<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT BUSH'S PLAN TO FIGHT DRUGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding President Bush's drug speech: 
</P>
<P>
First I read in the paper what he was going to say. 
</P>
<P>
Then I heard on the news what he was going to say. 
</P>
<P>
Then I heard on the news what he did say (with sound bites), what he should or 
could have said, and what it all means, if anything. 
</P>
<P>
Then I read in the paper what he did say (with verbatim quotes), what he should 
or could have said, and what it all means, if anything. 
</P>
<P>
In between there President Bush may actually have made a speech, though why he 
would bother is beyond me. The speech itself seems to be the least important 
part of the process. 
</P>
<P>
No wonder we are losing our ability to make decisions based on our own 
experience -- we are being denied the opportunity to have our own experience. 
</P>
<P>
KATHARINA SMITH 
</P>
<P>
Canoga Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
