<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Circle K Corp.: The Phoenix-based convenience store chain said first-quarter 
net income fell 39% to $7.6 million from a year ago. Revenue rose 24% to $1.02 
billion. The company said higher interest and depreciation costs related to an 
expansion program kept profits lower than in last year's first quarter. 
However, it also noted that after losing money in the final quarter of fiscal 
1989, the company did return to profitability. 
</P>
