<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DEDICATED DIGGERS AND PLANTERS: GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Bedding begonias can give you immediate color in the late summer or fall garden 
and can be counted on for a repeat performance next spring. 
</P>
<P>
When cutting flowers to fill indoor vases, make clean cuts with sharp clippers 
or a knife; these cuts will heal faster than ragged edges. 
</P>
<P>
Take inventory of the garden: Snip off infected leaves, dead flowers and 
awkward shoots; you'll get better, more continuous blooms by keeping faded 
blooms trimmed. 
</P>
<P>
Don't fertilize your lawn just before leaving on vacation. Tender new growth 
could suffer if there's a heat wave while you're gone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; List 
</P>
