<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 HELD AFTER CHASE IN ROBBERY OF S&amp;L 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of two men arrested Friday after an armed robbery at the Home Federal 
Savings &amp; Loan office at 6902 Navajo Road might be linked to a series of 
recent bank robberies, San Diego police said . 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested Bradley T. Hendon, 29, and Wayne K. Dyer, 30, after two men 
took $1,486 from the S&amp;L. 
</P>
<P>
"We think that Hendon has been involved in a series of robberies," a police 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Hendon and Dyer were arrested shortly before 5 p.m. after a brief chase. A 
search of their vehicle turned up an air gun resembling a .45-caliber pistol, 
as well as the missing cash. 
</P>
<P>
The two men were being held at the federal Metropolitan Correctional Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
