<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, 3 Bombs, 30 Guns Are Found Santa Ana and county bomb squad officers 
Friday approach a converted school bus used as a trailer by a Santa Ana man who 
had been arrested and charged in a stabbing incident last week. Authorities, 
having obtained a warrant to search the man's car and bus, which were impounded 
after his arrest, on Friday found three homemade bombs, about 30 handguns and 
rifles, and 1,000 rounds of ammunition and bomb-making materials, said Santa 
Ana Police Sgt. Rich Murg. The bombs were safely defused, said Murg, adding 
that the man, Richard Dean Woodley, 35, will now face weapons charges in 
addition to his assault charge. Murg said investigators have not determined how 
the explosives were to be used. MARK BOSTER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
