<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SAN DIEGO STATE SWEEPS FULLERTON IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego State defeated Cal State Fullerton, 15-5, 15-10, 15-6, in the 
championship round of the Collegiate Premiere tournament Friday in the Titan 
Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Rachel Wittliff had 12 kills and Stephanie Shrieve had 32 assists for 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State advanced to the second round. Fullerton plays USC at 12:30 p.m. 
today in both teams' final match of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton had advanced to the championship bracket by defeating Washington 
State, 15-9, 12-15, 15-12, 7-15, 17-15, in the last round of pool play. 
Fullerton won pool four with a 3-0 record. 
</P>
<P>
In the first match, freshman outside hitter Wittliff had 20 kills. 
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals: UC Santa Barbara plays San Diego State and BYU plays 
California, both at 12:30 p.m. The final is at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
In the Chapman College men's soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 1, Southern California College 0 -- Jeff Hudson scored with about two 
minutes left for host Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State 1, UC Irvine 0 -- Marcelo Balboa scored in the first half for 
visiting San Diego State./ 
</P>
</TEXT>
