<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA; 
</P>
<P>
SDSU NEGOTIATES RENT REDUCTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CURT HOLBREICH VOLLEYBALL San Diego State defeated Cal State Fullerton, 
15-5, 15-10, 15-6, in its first game of the championship round at 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego Stadium Authority Board has approved a reduction in rental terms 
with San Diego State for football games at San Diego Jack Murphy Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The changes, approved by the board Thursday and sent to the City Council for 
its consideration, could save SDSU about $14,000 this year, said Jim Herrick, 
SDSU assistant athletic director for finance. 
</P>
<P>
Herrick said the agreement is expected to cut in half a rent increase scheduled 
to take effect this year under provisions of a 10-year lease that expires in 
1993. He said without the reduction, the school would have expected to pay 
about $130,000 in rent for its seven 1989 home games. 
</P>
<P>
Herrick said agreement was also reached in three other areas: The authority 
agreed to exempt preferred seating donations from its rental fees and limit its 
share of cable television revenue, and the school agreed to a reduced seating 
configuration. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU requested the rent reduction after the Chargers renegotiated provisions of 
their lease last year, said Jack McGrory, assistant city manager. The SDSU 
athletic department has been hurt the past two fiscal years by falling 
attendance at home football games and a rising deficit. CURT 
HOLBREICHVOLLEYBALL San Diego State defeated Cal State Fullerton, 15-5, 15-10, 
15-6, in its first game of the championship round at the Collegiate Premiere 
tournament at Fullerton. SDSU advanced despite losing an earlier match to Cal, 
6-15, 15-11, 15-9, 15-10. Against Fullerton, Angela Martin had 14 kills. Angie 
Rais had eight kills and seven digs, but the University of San Diego (0-5) was 
defeated at Texas Tech, 15-11, 8-15, 7-15, 4-15.MEN'S SOCCER Point Loma 
Nazarene (1-0-1) tied UC San Diego, 0-0, to break the Tritons' 13-match winning 
streak dating back to last season. UCSD extended its unbeaten string to 26 
matches with the season-opening tie at the North Campus Stadium. SDSU defeated 
Cal Irvine, 1-0, in a nonconference match.WATER POLO Jason Brown scored 14 
goals to lead UC San Diego to victory in three matches at the UC Santa Barbara 
tournament. The Tritons defeated Loyola Marymount, 13-4, Cal State Los Angeles, 
15-7, and Occidental, 25-0.TRIATHLON Del Mar's Scott Tinley, 32, the perennial 
champion of the San Diego triathlon before Mike Pigg's 1988 victory, will try 
to take his title back from Pigg Sunday morning when the U.S. Triathlon Series 
makes its annual stop in North County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
