<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHRIMPER BLOCKADE FAILS IN LOUISIANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HARLINGEN, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The newly reinstated rule requiring Gulf Coast shrimpers to put turtle-escape 
doors on their nets drew scattered protests Friday, including an apparently 
unsuccessful blockade in Louisiana waters. 
</P>
<P>
Critics complain that too much of the catch escapes with the endangered turtles 
because they must use so-called turtle excluder devices (TEDs). 
</P>
<P>
Shrimpers in Louisiana set up a 30-boat blockade of a shipping channel Friday 
morning, Coast Guard officials said, but ships were able to navigate around 
them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
