<HEADLINE>
<P>
BISCUITS KILL 9 CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JAKARTA, Indonesia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least nine children died and 10 more were hospitalized after eating 
biscuits, the newspaper Kompas said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Azof, head of the South Sumatra Health Office, told the newspaper the 
poisoning was caused by too much sodium nitrate, a preservative. Police 
arrested two distributors of the biscuits, the newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
