<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LA HABRA; 
</P>
<P>
REDEVELOPMENT PLAN IS SUBJECT OF HEARING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The La Habra Redevelopment Agency will have a public hearing Sept. 19 on its 
five-year plan to spend $84 million to improve parks, widen streets and create 
new parking spaces downtown. 
</P>
<P>
The Resource Allocation Plan envisions eight major projects, and it is subject 
to regular reviews. 
</P>
<P>
Already under way are the expansion of the county library, improvements to 
Portola Park, the widening of La Habra Boulevard and the creation of new 
parking spaces in the downtown area. 
</P>
<P>
The most ambitious plans involve more than 115 acres scattered throughout the 
city. The $52-million project, authorized last July, involves commercial and 
industrial developments. 
</P>
<P>
One major feature is the demolition, to begin next year, of most of the Fashion 
Square Shopping Center at the northeast corner of Beach Boulevard and Imperial 
Highway. 
</P>
<P>
Also included is a plan to replace the drive-in theater at the southeast corner 
of Imperial Highway and Idaho Street with a 200,000-square-foot retail center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
