<HEADLINE>
<P>
VILLA PARK POUNDS BOLSA GRANDE, 45-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sometimes everything goes right for a football player. Take Gary Bladow, for 
example. Virtually every time Bladow carried the ball for Villa Park High 
School Friday night against Bolsa Grande, something good happened for the 
Spartans. 
</P>
<P>
Bladow only rushed 11 times, but he gained 112 yards, and his two touchdowns 
were a big reason for Villa Park's 45-0 victory. 
</P>
<P>
The problem for Bolsa Grande was that the night was going well for the rest of 
the Spartan backfield as well. Craig Moresco ran for 69 yards; Shane Norris ran 
for 47 and Shawn Potter ran for 35 yards and two touchdowns. Quarterback Jason 
Martian completed three of his seven passes for 61 yards and a touchdown. You 
get the picture. 
</P>
<P>
"We'll take the points when we get them," said Villa Park coach Pat Mahoney. 
"They were hard to come by last year." 
</P>
<P>
This Spartan defense didn't allow Bolsa to come close to the end zone. Of 
course, Bolsa didn't give itself much of a chance as it fumbled away its first 
three possessions. And on the fourth, with Bolsa already behind 9-0, Villa 
Park's Garrett Johnson tacked Bolsa punter Tim Desrosiers on the one-yard line 
after Desrosiers ran down an errant snap. 
</P>
<P>
Bladow followed with one of his touchdowns and the game was all but over with 
the Spartans leading, 17-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
